cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper deals with medical image segmentation using deep convolutional networks and proposes a domain adaptation method for adapting segmentation networks between different modalities of medical images. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also uses adversarial learning, which is a popular technique in deep learning, so cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also a likely category. The paper also proposes a novel benchmark on the cardiac dataset, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper deals with adapting networks to different domains, which could also fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
